The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

                                        Archives
                                                                                                                                    The City Diary

        A red alert has been issued at Netaji Subhas Chandra Bose International Airport from January 21 to 29, officials said on Sunday. A CISF official said the alert was issued for Republic Day. Visitors will not be allowed into the domestic and international terminals during the period.
  Officials of Lake Town police station arrested two youths, Somnath Biswas and Mrityunjoy Ghosh, both residents of Baguiati, on charges of molesting a doctor near Lake Town on Friday night. According to police, the victim, accompanied by her husband, was coming towards Bangur in a car when one of the front tyres burst. When the couple got off the car to change the tyre, three youths who were passing by tried to molest the woman. A police patrol team rushed over on hearing the womans screams and arrested the duo. The third managed to flee.
  Trouble broke out in a nursing home at Joramandir on Sunday morning after the relatives of a 35-year-old woman, Tanjora Biwi, who died of burns, refused to allow the nursing home authorities to inform police and conduct a post-mortem. A team from Baguiati police station went to the spot and brought the situation under control.
  A 50-year-old unidentified man was run over by a truck on Paharpur Road, in Garden Reach, early on Sunday. The truck driver fled in his vehicle.
                                                                             
